uk.ac.manchester.cs.mekon.owl.reason

Class OROntologyLinkedMatcher

  • java.lang.Object
    • uk.ac.manchester.cs.mekon.network.NMatcher
      • uk.ac.manchester.cs.mekon.owl.reason.OROntologyLinkedMatcher
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IMatcher
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    ORMatcher, OTMatcher

    public abstract class OROntologyLinkedMatcher
extends NMatcher
    Abstract base-class for OWL ontology-linked implementations of the matching mechanisms defined by IMatcher.

    This class is an abstract extention of NMatcher, and hence operates on pre-processable instantiations of the network-based representations. These network-based instantiations are passed to appropriate abstract methods, whose implementations will convert them to appropriate OWL constructs and perform the required reasoning operations.

    Before being passed on to the abstract methods, the network-based instantiations are pre-processed to ensure "ontology-compliance". This ensures that they will only contain entities for which equivalents exist in, or for which substitutions can be made from, the relevant ontology. Hence, any nodes whose associated concepts do not have equivalents in the ontology, will either be modified to reference appropriate ancestor-concepts (as determined by looking at the frames model), or else removed from the network. Also, any links whose associated properties do not have equivalents in the ontology will be removed from the network.
